Package com.github.tommyettinger.ds.support.util

Interface FloatIterator

All Superinterfaces:
Iterator<Float>, PrimitiveIterator<Float,FloatConsumer>
All Known Implementing Classes:
FloatDeque.FloatDequeIterator, FloatList.FloatListIterator, IntFloatMap.ValueIterator, LongFloatMap.ValueIterator, ObjectFloatMap.ValueIterator
public interface FloatIterator extends PrimitiveIterator<Float,FloatConsumer>
An Iterator specialized for float values. This is a PrimitiveIterator, like the existing PrimitiveIterator.OfInt and PrimitiveIterator.OfLong interfaces, but it can't be a nested interface like those because it is defined outside of the JDK.

    • forEachRemaining

      default void forEachRemaining(FloatConsumer action)
      Performs the given action for each remaining element until all elements have been processed or the action throws an exception. Actions are performed in the order of iteration, if that order is specified. Exceptions thrown by the action are relayed to the caller.
      Specified by:
      forEachRemaining in interface PrimitiveIterator<Float,FloatConsumer>
      Parameters:
      action - The action to be performed for each element
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - if the specified action is null
      "Implementation Requirements"

      The default implementation behaves as if: 

      
     while (hasNext())
         action.accept(nextFloat());

    • forEachRemaining

      default void forEachRemaining(Consumer<? super Float> action)
      Specified by:
      forEachRemaining in interface Iterator<Float>
      "Implementation Requirements"
      If the action is an instance of LongConsumer then it is cast to LongConsumer and passed to forEachRemaining(com.github.tommyettinger.ds.support.function.FloatConsumer); otherwise the action is adapted to an instance of LongConsumer, by boxing the argument of LongConsumer, and then passed to forEachRemaining(com.github.tommyettinger.ds.support.function.FloatConsumer).
